Your Honor,

I stand before you today as a 25-year-old defendant, Olivia Jones, pleading guilty to the offense of stealing 1000 pounds from the cash register at the café where I used to work. I want to express my deep remorse for my actions and take full responsibility for the harm I have caused.

I acknowledge that I abused the trust of my former boss by taking small amounts of money each week from the cash register. I realize now the gravity of my actions, and I sincerely apologize for the pain and inconvenience I have caused her.

I want to emphasize that I have no prior criminal record, which I believe demonstrates that this is an isolated incident and not indicative of my character as a whole.

While I am unable to make immediate restitution due to the loss of my job, I want to assure the court that I am committed to accepting the consequences of my actions. I understand the seriousness of the offense I have committed and the importance of personal growth in ensuring I do not repeat such behavior in the future. Moving forward, I am determined to make positive changes in my life.

Your Honor, I acknowledge that my plea of guilty is in itself a mitigating factor. I accept the consequences of my actions and am prepared to cooperate fully with any sentencing that the court deems appropriate.

While I understand the impact of my crime and the need for accountability, I kindly request the court to consider the factors outlined above. I genuinely regret my actions and am committed to learning from this experience and contributing positively to society.

Thank you for your attention, Your Honor.
